paragraph
 Not eXactly C, or NXC, is a high-level programming language for the Lego Mindstorms NXT designed by John Hansen in 2006. NXC, which is short for Not eXactly C, is based on Next Byte Codes, an assembly language. NXC has a syntax like C. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Not_eXactly_C">Read more on Wikipedia...</a>

